pullRequest.body:
We construct the Lie algebra of a real or complex Lie group, where the bracket is given by the vector field bracket of invariant vector fields associated to an element of the Lie algebra, i.e., the tangent space at the identity. The Jacobi identity follows from the fact that it is satisfied generally by the Lie bracket of vector fields.

Along the way, we define the Lie bracket of vector fields, first in vector spaces and then in manifolds. The notion is only well behaved in manifolds when changes of charts have a symmetric second derivative, which is currently only available in mathlib for maps over R or C. Once analytic manifolds enter the smooth hierarchy in #17152, we will easily get the same theory for analytic manifolds, and therefore the Lie algebra of a Lie group over a general field.
